{"Id":"CG189","LastModified":"2024-06-14T08:05:25.8422023Z","ProductType":"CG","Title":"Obesity: identification, assessment and management ","ShortTitle":null,"InDevReference":"CG/Wave0/682","MetaDescription":"This guideline covers identifying, assessing and managing obesity in children (aged 2 years and over), young people and adults\n","Summary":"<p class=\"lead\">This guideline covers identifying, assessing and managing obesity in children (aged 2 years and over), young people and adults.</p>\n<p>In&nbsp;<strong>July 2023</strong>, we reviewed the evidence on bariatric surgery for people living with overweight and obesity and updated the <a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg189/chapter/Recommendations#surgical-interventions\">recommendations on surgical interventions</a>.</p>\n<p>NICE has also produced <a href=\"http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/CG43\">guidelines on obesity prevention</a>, <a href=\"http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ng7\">maintaining a healthy weight</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ph53\">managing overweight and obesity in adults</a> and in <a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ph47\">children and young people</a>.</p>\n<h2>Recommendations</h2>\n<p>This guideline includes recommendations on:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg189/chapter/Recommendations#generic-principles-of-care\">principles of care</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg189/chapter/Recommendations#identifying-and-assessing-overweight-obesity-and-central-adiposity\">identifying and assessing overweight, obesity and central adiposity</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg189/chapter/1-Recommendations#assessment\">assessment</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg189/chapter/1-Recommendations#lifestyle-interventions\">lifestyle</a>, <a href=\"http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg189/chapter/1-Recommendations#behavioural-interventions\">behavioural</a>, <a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg189/chapter/Recommendations#dietary-approaches\">dietary</a> and <a href=\"http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg189/chapter/1-Recommendations#pharmacological-interventions\">pharmacological</a> interventions</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg189/chapter/1-Recommendations#physical-activity\">physical activity</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg189/chapter/1-Recommendations#surgical-interventions\">bariatric surgery</a>, including <a href=\"http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg189/chapter/1-Recommendations#when-to-offer-expedited-assessment\">when to offer expedited assessment</a> and <a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/cg189/chapter/Recommendations#follow-up-care\">follow-up care</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Who is it for?</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Healthcare professionals</li>\n<li>Commissioners and providers</li>\n<li>People who are living with obesity and their families and carers</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Is this guideline up to date?</h2>\n<p>We are updating our suite of guidelines on weight management. See the <a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/indevelopment/gid-ng10182\">guideline in development page</a> for progress on the update.</p>\n<h2>Guideline development process</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.nice.org.uk/about/what-we-do/our-programmes/nice-guidance/nice-guidelines/how-we-develop-nice-guidelines\">How we develop NICE guidelines</a></p>\n<p>This guideline replaces NICE guideline PH46 (July 2013) and&nbsp;updates and replaces section 1.2 of NICE guideline CG43 (December 2006).</p>\n<p>This guideline was previously called obesity: identification, assessment and management of overweight and obesity in children, young people and adults.</p>","WithdrawnNotes":"","ProductStatus":"Published","VersionNumber":43,"PublishedDate":"2014-11-27T00:00:00","LastMajorModificationDate":"2023-07-26T00:00:00","MajorChangeDate":"2023-07-26T00:00:00","NextReviewDate":null,"CollectionTypesList":[],"AuthorList":["National Insti